Title: Brick & Steel: Full Retired
Credit: Written by
Author: Stu Maschwitz
Source: Adapted from story by KTM
Draft date: 1/27/2012
Notes: Period live-action buddy-cop action comedy. Closed cast; keep looks stable across scenes.

INT. BRICK'S PATIO - DAY

A gorgeous day. The sun is shining. BRICK BRADDOCK, retired police detective, mid-fifties, solid build, short salt-and-pepper hair, weathered face, casual polo and khakis, sits quietly on the patio, contemplating -- something.

The SCREEN DOOR slides open. DICK STEEL, his former partner and fellow retiree, mid-fifties, leaner athletic build, close-cropped dark hair going gray, easy grin, Hawaiian shirt and jeans, emerges with two cold beers.

STEEL
Beer's ready!

BRICK
Are they cold?

STEEL
Does a bear crap in the woods?

Steel sits. They laugh at the dumb joke.

STEEL
(beer raised)
To retirement.

BRICK
To retirement.

They drink long and well from the beers.

And then there's a long beat.
Longer than is funny.
Long enough to be depressing.

The men look at each other.

STEEL
Screw retirement.

BRICK ^
Screw retirement.

SMASH CUT TO:

INT. TRAILER HOME - DAY

Home of THE BOY BAND -- DAN and JACK. Dan, thirties, wiry, dark hair, flashy street clothes; Jack, thirties, stockier, tattooed forearms, matching hustler look. They drink beer and count the take from their last smash-and-grab. Money, drugs, and ridiculous props strewn across the table.

JACK
(in Vietnamese, subtitled)
Did you know Brick and Steel are retired?

DAN
Then let's retire them.
Permanently.

Jack begins to argue vociferously in Vietnamese. Mercifully we--

CUT TO:

EXT. BRICK'S POOL - DAY

Steel, phone clamped to his ear, in the middle of a heated call. Pool glitters behind him.

STEEL
They're coming out of the woodwork!

(pause)

No, everybody we've put away!

(pause)

Point Blank Sniper?

SNIPER SCOPE POV

From what seems like only INCHES AWAY. Steel's face FILLS the Leupold Mark 4 scope.

STEEL
The man's a myth!

Steel turns and looks straight into the cross-hairs.

STEEL
(oh crap)
Hello...

CUT TO:

EXT. OPENING TITLES - DAY

Bold title cards smash on:

BRICK BRADDOCK
& DICK STEEL IN

BRICK & STEEL
FULL RETIRED

SMASH CUT TO:

EXT. WOODEN SHACK - DAY

COGNITO, criminal mastermind, forties, slicked hair, cheap suit, sweaty and rattled, is SLAMMED against the wall.

COGNITO
Woah woah woah, Brick and Steel!

Sure enough -- Brick and Steel, roughing up their favorite usual suspect.

COGNITO
What is it you want with me, DICK?

Steel SMACKS him.

STEEL
Who's coming after us?

COGNITO
Everyone's coming after you mate! Scorpio, The Boy Band, Sparrow, Point Blank Sniper...

As he rattles off the long list, Brick and Steel share a look. This is going to be BAD.

CUT TO:

INT. GARAGE - DAY

Brick and Steel climb into Mom's PORSCHE -- Steel at the wheel. They pause for a beat, the gravity of the situation catching up with them.

BRICK
This is everybody we've ever put away.

STEEL
(starting the engine)
So much for retirement!

They speed off. To destiny.

CUT TO:

EXT. PALATIAL MANSION - DAY

An EXTREMELY HANDSOME MAN, forties, chiseled, shirtless, drinks a beer on a sunlit terrace.

His MINION, nondescript henchman in a dark suit, approaches.

MINION
We found Brick and Steel!

HANDSOME MAN
I want them dead. DEAD!

Beer flies.

FADE TO PINK.

THE END
